<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dudeman</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Does the order in which quests are completed and areas are cleared really matter?  Assuming that the experience you get from killing baddies degrades at a constant rate, do you end up with the same amount of total experience at the end of the game?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alrik Fassbauer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I know of no necessary order in conjunction witz Experience Points.<P>There is a certain degraa of degradation  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/wink.gif"> : At some Point (high level), you don't get Experience Points anymore for really weak enemies, like snakes, for example, that's what Lar once said.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Serops</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Quest experience increases as you gain levels, while experience from monsters decreases.  Depending on how you do things you might end up with a different total at the end, but I don't think it matters too much (the game get's easy enough that a level or two shouldn't make a difference).  I wouldn't worry about it.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">the bean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">what i also remember is that there IS a difference in the order you do quest..<BR>somewere in te forum theer was someone who openend the catacombs in the first village (the dragon stues) before consulting Lnilor/ardinus<P>he get lesser exp then he would if talked first to them...<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Alarys</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The order of quests will matter, since doing them in certain ways breaks other quests and makes them unavailable/uncompletable. Thus, you lose the potential for getting experience for them.<P>As was pointed out, don't worry about it too much, unless you obsess over completing as many quests as possible, and hate having uncompleted quests in your journal (I fit into that category, rofl ;-)</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ratbag</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">** small early game spoiler **<P>What about timed quests? How many of these are there? One I ran across was the quest to cure the two soldiers in Aleroth. I let this one go for about two weeks of game time and I checked my quest log to find that this quest was listed as failed. Anyone run across other quests like this?</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">SensoO</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Ratbag:<BR><I>** small early game spoiler **<P>What about timed quests? How many of these are there? One I ran across was the quest to cure the two soldiers in Aleroth. I let this one go for about two weeks of game time and I checked my quest log to find that this quest was listed as failed. Anyone run across other quests like this?</I><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>TWO WEEKS!?!? Well, of course you failed. They were sick enough to need magic healing were they not? They had to die eventually... Actually, completing the catacombs before tending to them seals their fate. Other than that, I've yet to see any other quests like that, but I'm still in the beginning of the game  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR>War happens, so just stay out of my way...</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Niku'a</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If you leave Aleroth before curing the two soldiers, they will die. And getting wisdom might help you get more xp too.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
